Eight people have been killed and thirteen others injured in two separate accidents on N2 between Mthatha and Dutywa in Eastern Cape.The accidents happened within a space of three hours on the same spot, it is reported that thirteen people with severe injuries were air lifted to a local hospital.In the first accident four people died while six seriously injured had to be airlifted near Nywara village outside Dutywa.It is believed that the accident happened when the Amathole district municipality bakkie and a Toyota Avanza collided head-on.After three hours later a second accident between a truck and a bakkie claimed four lives and seven were injured.Although Police are still investigating both accident, it is suspected that the second accident could have happened because of the road had not been thoroughly cleared after the first fatal accident.TNA Reporter 